div1.p: 1390. In the United States Circuit Court for the Western District of Washington, Northern Division.
In the matter of the application of Columbia George for a writ of Habeas Corpus.
Filed in the U.S. Circuit Court. JUN 21 1905, A.Reeves Ayres, Clerk.
In the United States Circuit Court for the Western Distric of Washington, Northern Division.
In the Matter of the Application of Columbia George, for a writ of Habeas Corpus. No. 1390.

To the Clerk of the above-entitled Court.
You will please prepare transcript of the record in this cause, to be filed in the office of the clerk of the United States Circuit Court of Appeals for the 9th Judicial Circuit, under the appeal heretofore perfected to said court and include in said transcript the following pleadings, proceedings and papers on file, to-wit: Petition for writ; Affidavit and order for leave to prosecute, as a poor person; Order to show cause; and acceptance of service; Application of U.S. Dis. Attorney for leave for United States to intervene; Order for United States to intervene; Order of the court setting time for hearing; The answer to the petition, and order to show cause; The reply to the cause; Order of court taking the matter under advisement; Exhibits offered by petitioner; Opinion of the court; Final orders, and exceptions; Petition for appeal and specification of errors; And order allowing the same; And all other papers and orders of record in said cause.

Said transcript to be prepared as required by law and the rules of this Court and the rules of the United States Circuit Court of appeals for the 9th Circuit and on file in the office of the clerk of the said Circuit Court of Appeals at San Francisco, before July 1st 1906.
